Project Structure
PasswordGenerator: Main class that contains the method for generating passwords based on user preferences.
User Interface: Command line interface to allow the user to specify options for password generation.

Code Explanation
Defining Character Sets:

There are four character sets: lowercase letters, uppercase letters, numbers, and symbols.
The generator starts with lowercase letters and adds the other sets based on the user's preferences.
User Input:

The user is prompted to specify the length of the password and whether to include uppercase letters, numbers, and symbols.
Password Generation:

Uses SecureRandom to generate a password securely.
The generatePassword method constructs the password using the selected character sets and the specified length.
Using SecureRandom:

The SecureRandom class is used to ensure that the password is generated randomly and securely.
How to Run the Project
Compile the PasswordGenerator.java file.
Run the program:
The program will prompt you for the length of the password and whether to include uppercase letters, numbers, and symbols.
After providing the information, the program will generate and display the password.